    {
      "id": "93",
      "name": "Lore",
      "components": [
        {
          "component_id": "customize",
          "data": {
            "data": {
              "parsed_content": [
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Idyia",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "A theatrical performance based on Idyia's story:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "The girl hailed from a kingdom that sat atop the waterfalls. but when the reigning dynasty fell and a new one seized power, she and her people fled for their lives. A thick fog began to fill the air as she made her way through the forest, and dense thickets tried to block her path.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"If only I had a lamp to guide me through this wretched forest… then I could survive…\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "With scratches covering her arms and legs, the girl pressed through the pain and made her way forward. The road ahead was arduous, but she was determined to press onward.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"I've come this far, and I’m not about to turn back now.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "But just as she was drawing near her destination, a huge stretch of thorns and brambles suddenly came into view. Despair set in and began to weigh on her heart.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"If only someone could help me… I would give anything in return.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "The girl's heartfelt wish in her moment of desperation did not go unheard… Her path was cleared, and so the girl continued her journey deeper into the forest. But what she found there was not a lamp, but a mage glowing with fire, who helped burn a path through the thicket. The mage took pity on the girl and handed her a bottle. Then, the mage began to tell the story of how the bottle came into her possession.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "The fiery mage had an adventurous spirit and enjoyed taking long journeys. On one such journey, while taking a rest in an oasis, she found a beautiful bottle by a crescent-shaped lake. She was an extraordinary mage with the power to grant people their wishes. She turned the bottle into a thing of equally extraordinary power. But the only place that it could make wishes come true was inside of the bottle. The fiery mage blew into the bottle, allowing it to grant one single wish outside its glass walls. A flame was kindled within the bottle, and it began to glow a fiery red, just like the mage herself.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "After the mage finished telling her story, she disappeared, leaving only the bottle behind.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"A magic bottle that can grant wishes… Then, I wish to leave this place, and go somewhere where no one will ever find me again…\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "The flame in the bottle faded as the girl's single wish was granted, and she found herself in the middle of the desert, far away, where no one could ever find her.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Idyia is an Oceanid, who was exiled when the former Hydro Archon passed away and waters became full of pain and hatred. She was wandering through the forest when she met Alice, a witch from the Hexenzierkel. It was Alice who gave Idyia a magic bottle, which can grant one wish inside the bottle itself. Idiya wished to go far away, where no one could find her, so she ended up in the middle of the desert.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/21/237301566/86ceaf03762c6ec439360750c275814f_5222240186364322151.jpg"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "She continued to live in the subspace, called the Veluriyam Mirage, inside the bottle. Rare wanderers, who were passing by, came to her abode, asking to grant their wishes. When they had to leave, some were angry that the wish was granted only inside the Veluriyam Mirage, but some left Idyia gifts, which she",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/21/237301566/fcc4cb5c1c65f7729366cae33ef0d58f_5408120009858089420.jpg"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "used for her adobe. Some wished to leave their mark on the Veluriyam Mirage, so Idyia made their copies with the help of Hydro eidolons, so she wouldn't be lonely. All eidolons represented the embodiment of the owners' desires.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Idyia is believed to be as powerful as Rhodeia, as she can not only take the human form, but also create Oceanid-humans from Eidolons.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 3979,
                      "icon_url": "https://upload-static.hoyoverse.com/hoyolab-wiki/2023/08/21/237301566/decfebf39c4d3b6e22cf9f28c98288f6_1758697124608038722.png",
                      "name": "Фонтейн",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 4924,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/01/05/237301566/5e33c09fbd3c6781bb822fd9c57b6abc_954472598676910116.png",
                      "name": "Океаниды",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 6367,
                      "icon_url": "",
                      "name": "Alice",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 4780,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-webstatic.hoyoverse.com/event-static-hoyowiki-admin/2023/12/20/a5b8d23dd3fbe0969cc3ebce78f9c29f_8021351765588020911.png",
                      "name": "Эгерия",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 4906,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/01/03/237301566/c1060c024385e4bf2d87aa853d3a6afe_4104670316167585665.png",
                      "name": "Родия",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Veluriyam Mirage",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://upload-static.hoyoverse.com/hoyolab-wiki/2023/07/14/237301566/67fa88a6d61e270be9cadcb5727ffb13_7400455253446521999.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "One summer, Klee received a letter from her mother Alice, in which she invited Klee to visit a friend in Sumeru. Klee asked the Traveler, Paimon, and Kaeya to go with her. In Sumeru, they searched for someone who had knowledge of the area and met Collei and Eula, who was searching for her relative.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://upload-static.hoyoverse.com/hoyolab-wiki/2023/07/14/237301566/d86494f8a95a29a72cacd320818404a8_528170365378851481.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Together they used the magic letter and were transported to the Veluriyam Mirage — a magical subspace created inside the bottle. There they met Alice's friend Idyia, who was the manager of Veluriyam Mirage, and Kokomi, the Divine Priestess of Watatsumi Island, who arrived at the Veluriyam Mirage on personal business.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://upload-static.hoyoverse.com/hoyolab-wiki/2023/07/14/237301566/3619cd3f90f4d66702a5d08a2e85add0_5098585023973143999.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "It turned out that shortly before they arrived in the Veluriyam Mirage, the main core of subspace had broken, so they volunteered to help Idyia fix it. While the Traveler was looking for the necessary parts of the core, they met other visitors to the Veluriyam Mirage, who all had blue hair and eyes, and Hydro Eidolons — Hydro creatures that resemble water droplets. When all the lost core pieces were finally collected, it was revealed that Idyia was an Oceanid, who settled in the Veluriyam Mirage and helped travelers who found themselves in the desert.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 4924,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/01/08/94376896/5e33c09fbd3c6781bb822fd9c57b6abc_7075433854813111066.png",
                      "name": "Oceanids",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 6367,
                      "icon_url": "",
                      "name": "Alice",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
